long_desc.thetext: Could you please add http://epsilonblog.wordpress.com to the list of blogs on PlanetEclipse?

Do you want to establish an "Eclipse" category on your blog so it's easy to just syndicate Eclipse-related posts?
I usually tag blog posts with 'eclipse' to make sure they are relevant.
The blog is dedicated to the Epsilon GMT component and so all posts are (and will be) Eclipse-related.
ok, that's all I need to hear
Could you please rename the label of the blog in the list from "Dimitrios Kolovos" to "Epsilon"?
I've just added a new article to the blog but in PlanetEclipse instead of the actual title, my name appears as the title of the post.
I think this is a wordpress issue if I recall, let me investigate a bit
Ian, did you have a similar issue with Wordpress? I don't remember what the solution was...

Yes I had a problem when I embedded images or pictures into a blog post. Nice work around was to just not do that...
Not sure what is the problem here. Sorry.

It's related to some feed "enhancements" which confuse our Planet. AFAIK it's caused by some profile picture that is published in your feed. Until we upgrade our Planet you need to turn off some image/personal picture publishing in your WordPress profile.

never mind, we can fix it on our side by appending a parameter to the feed
http://epsilonblog.wordpress.com/feed/?mrss=off
